    <mj-section>
      <mj-column width="100%">
        <mj-text padding-bottom="0px">
          <h2 style="font-weight: bold">Tools</h2>
          <p><a href="https://monzo.com/blog/controlling-outbound-traffic-from-kubernetes">Controlling outbound traffic from Kubernetes</a><br />
            This is brilliant and intense. This is how you keep bad shit from running in your cluster. A little automation and you can find leaky points in your processes and infrastructure at a moment&rsquo;s notice.</p>

          <p><a href="https://liquidat.wordpress.com/2020/04/09/getting-started-with-ansible-security-automation-investigation-enrichment/">Getting Started with Ansible Security Automation: Investigation Enrichment</a><br />
            &ldquo;In this blog post we have a closer look at how Ansible can help to overcome these challenges and support investigation enrichment activities. In the following example we'll see how Ansible can be used to enable programmatic access to information like logs coming from technologies that may not be integrated into a SIEM.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://info.crunchydata.com/blog/optimize-postgresql-server-performance">Optimize PostgreSQL Server Performance Through Configuration</a><br />
            [I]t&rsquo;s always recommended that one of the first actions performed once an install of PostgreSQL is completed, would be to tune and configure some high-level settings.</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.percona.com/blog/2020/04/10/percona-xtrabackup-backup-and-restore-of-a-single-table-or-database/">Percona XtraBackup: Backup and Restore of a Single Table or Database</a><br />
            Percona tools have saved my ass more times than I can count. Give this a read in case you ever end up in a MySQL pickle.</p>

          <p><a href="https://spectrum.ieee.org/automaton/robotics/home-robots/irobot-launches-robot-simulator-free-online-curriculum-for-robotics-education">iRobot Launches Robot Simulator, Free Online Curriculum for Robotics Education</a><br />
            &ldquo;Your kids can learn to program robots from scratch, for free, on their computer or phone&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/about-aws/whats-new/2020/04/aws-fargate-launches-platform-version-14/">AWS Fargate launches Platform Version 1.4</a><br />
            Still not the container management platform we want (see last week&rsquo;s issue).</p>

          <p><a href="https://product.hubspot.com/blog/zookeeper-to-kubernetes-migration">Embrace and Replace: Migrating ZooKeeper into Kubernetes</a><br />
            &ldquo;We recently migrated hundreds of ZooKeeper instances from individual server instances to Kubernetes without downtime. Our approach used powerful Kubernetes features like endpoints to ease the process, so we're sharing the high level outline of the approach for anyone who wants to follow in our footsteps.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://kerestey.net/writing/2020-04-05-announcing-unverified-dot-email.html">Announcing unverified.email</a><br />
            &ldquo;unverified.email is a catch-all SMTP server. You can use it programmatically via its API at <a href="https://api.unverified.email">https://api.unverified.email</a>, and the article shows an example of its usage.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://markmap.js.org/">markmap-lib</a><br />
            Turn Markdown into a mind map. I&rsquo;m going to have some fun with this later.</p>

          <p><a href="https://github.com/ManagedKube/kubernetes-common-services">ManagedKube/kubernetes-common-services</a><br />
            &ldquo;These services help make it easier to manage your applications environment in Kubernetes&rdquo;</p>
        </mj-text>
